    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Injustice in Peru</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>James W Hamilton letter on Sept 27 article questions why Peru does not pursue charges against flagrant civil rights abuser Vladimiro Montesinos, but continues to jail Lori Berenson0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>If the Peruvian government is willing to let Vladimiro Montesinos, the disgraced Peruvian intelligence chief and a flagrant abuser of civil rights, flee to Panama and to drop bribery charges against him (news article, Sept. 27), how can it justify keeping Lori Berenson, the young American, in prison?</p>
        <p>JAMES W. HAMILTON  Santa Fe, N.M., Sept. 28, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>If the Peruvian government is willing to let Vladimiro Montesinos, the disgraced Peruvian intelligence chief and a flagrant abuser of civil rights, flee to Panama and to drop bribery charges against him (news article, Sept. 27), how can it justify keeping Lori Berenson, the young American, in prison?</p>
        <p>JAMES W. HAMILTON  Santa Fe, N.M., Sept. 28, 2000</p>
      </block>
